<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><rss xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" version="2.0"><channel><title><![CDATA[Christian Predebon]]></title><description><![CDATA[Personal website of Christian Predebon]]></description><link>https://christianpredebon.it</link><generator>GatsbyJS</generator><lastBuildDate>Fri, 15 May 2020 12:50:45 GMT</lastBuildDate><item><title><![CDATA[Hello world]]></title><description><![CDATA[This is my first attempt at a blog. I'm not a journalist and I don't want to be, I just wanted a safe corner where I could publish some…]]></description><link>https://christianpredebon.it/2020/02/16-02-2020-hello-world/</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://christianpredebon.it/2020/02/16-02-2020-hello-world/</guid><pubDate>Invalid Date</pubDate><content:encoded>&lt;p&gt;This is my first attempt at a blog. I&apos;m not a journalist and I don&apos;t want to be, I just wanted a safe corner where I could publish some opinions and some programming related stuff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m also quite young and I&apos;m relatively new of programming, so you will see a lot of &lt;em&gt;What x is used for?&lt;/em&gt; articles about a technology that I learned two days before.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I want to focus this blog on few things:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;functional programming using mainly &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.typescriptlang.org/&quot;&gt;typescript&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;web design&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;UX/UI&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;maybe&lt;/em&gt; books (I love read as you can see &lt;a href=&quot;https://christianpredebon.it/&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t know how it will end but I hope to be able to bring good content and interesting topic.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I haven&apos;t any newsletter, but if you think it might be interest you, feel free to link my &lt;a href=&quot;https://christianpredebon.it/rss.xml&quot;&gt;rss&lt;/a&gt; feed inside something like &lt;a href=&quot;https://nodetics.com/feedbro/&quot;&gt;feedbro&lt;/a&gt; or just check back in a while.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title><![CDATA[The hard of choosing a CSS framework]]></title><description><![CDATA[Every time when I start a new project, be it a web application, a blog or a new website, I face the same question. Lot of you may think at…]]></description><link>https://christianpredebon.it/2020/03/12-03-2020-the-hard-of-choosing-a-css-framework/</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://christianpredebon.it/2020/03/12-03-2020-the-hard-of-choosing-a-css-framework/</guid><pubDate>Wed, 02 Dec 2020 23:00:00 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded>&lt;p&gt;Every time when I start a new project, be it a web application, a blog or a new website, I face the same question.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;h2 style=&quot;text-align: center;font-style: italic;&quot;&gt;Which CSS framework should I use this time?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lot of you may think at this question as useless, &lt;em&gt;why do I have to choose a different framework every time when I already know the potential of one that I have already used?&lt;/em&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The reason is simple and it&apos;s because we have a looot of framework out there.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://getbootstrap.com/&quot;&gt;Bootstrap&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://semantic-ui.com/&quot;&gt;Semantic UI&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bulma.io/&quot;&gt;Bulma&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.muicss.com/&quot;&gt;MUI&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://getuikit.com/&quot;&gt;UIKit&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://primer.style/&quot;&gt;Primer&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://getbase.org/&quot;&gt;Base&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://materializecss.com/&quot;&gt;Materialize&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://picturepan2.github.io/spectre/&quot;&gt;Spectre&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://spiderpig86.github.io/Cirrus/&quot;&gt;Cirrus&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://milligram.io/&quot;&gt;Milligram&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://tailwindcss.com/&quot;&gt;Tailwindcss&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.getpapercss.com/&quot;&gt;PaperCSS&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I ended here the list but really, it could go on much longer than that. I thought it was enough to make you understand the range of options we have available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Anyway, although the set is wide, with many mistakes I understood that not all solutions answer all the questions, for this reason over time I tried to identify which aspects I think should be taken into consideration in order to choose the right framework.
&lt;h3&gt;LANGUAGE&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lot of frameworks are written in &lt;a href=&quot;https://sass-lang.com/&quot;&gt;SCSS&lt;/a&gt;, other in &lt;a href=&quot;http://lesscss.org/&quot;&gt;LESS&lt;/a&gt; and other again in plain CSS. Choose based on the language you feel more comfortable with.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;RESPONSIVENESS&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Since I guess you won&apos;t want spend most of your time writing &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.w3schools.com/css/css_rwd_mediaqueries.asp&quot;&gt;media queries&lt;/a&gt;, choose a framework that it&apos;s mobile-ready, that therefore does not require modifications to work well on a phone rather than on a tablet.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;FEATURES&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Each framework offers a wide range of features out of the box, from the simple button to the spinner for the loading time. Identifies the components you want to use and considers choosing a framework based on the availability of its components.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;h2 style=&quot;text-align: center;font-style: italic;&quot;&gt;What is the target of this new application, what type of users will have to use it and in which area?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
One of the fundamental things for choosing a CSS framework is precisely identifying by whom the application will be used, who will be the main user and where it will be used (I mean the place, an office rather than a field of land). 
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
This information will help you to complete the project in the best way.
&lt;p&gt;For instance:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If the application is to be used by a fifth grade class then I head towards a solution that prefers simple lines, the use of many colors and plenty of &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.w3schools.com/css/css_padding.asp&quot;&gt;padding&lt;/a&gt;, something like &lt;a href=&quot;https://bulma.io/&quot;&gt;Bulma&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If I have to present my application to bankers, then I can opt for a more sober solution, that leaves no room for too many frills, which does not distract too much from what must be the main functionality, something like &lt;a href=&quot;https://semantic-ui.com/&quot;&gt;Sematic UI&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Again, if the application is to be used in the middle of a field of land by a farmer wearing gloves, then I am concerned that the CSS framework has an option to make the buttons large enough to be pressed by a finger covered with a glove.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All these examples to underline that each environment and each area searches for a product in which to reflect itself, and the main task of a good developer is to understand and better tail the product to these characteristics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title><![CDATA[The hard of choosing a CSS framework]]></title><description><![CDATA[One of the most common things while writing a dynamic web application with React is forms. In general, in almost all web application you…]]></description><link>https://christianpredebon.it/2020/04/05-04-2020-safe-form-in-react/</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://christianpredebon.it/2020/04/05-04-2020-safe-form-in-react/</guid><pubDate>Wed, 02 Dec 2020 23:00:00 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded>&lt;p&gt;One of the most common things while writing a dynamic web application with React is &lt;a href=&quot;https://reactjs.org/docs/forms.html&quot;&gt;forms&lt;/a&gt;. In general, in almost all web application you will find a form to compile in order to achieve something, for example for a newsletter subscription or for sending informations to the server.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Let&apos;s write a simple form with this requirements:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;an input for the firstname&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;an input for the lastname&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;a submit button for sending the compiled information&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will write it in three different way, from time to time always in a more abstract way.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Also, in this post I&apos;ll use React hooks because I think it&apos;s the standard nowadays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Before starting let&apos;s write an input components and an &lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;isEmpty&lt;/code&gt; function for simplicity of use in the next examples.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;gatsby-highlight&quot; data-language=&quot;tsx&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;language-tsx&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-tsx&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;interface&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token class-name&quot;&gt;InputProps&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
  value&lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token builtin&quot;&gt;string&lt;/span&gt;
  onChange&lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;value&lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; React&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;ChangeEvent&lt;span class=&quot;token tag&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token tag&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token class-name&quot;&gt;HTMLInputElement&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token plain-text&quot;&gt;) =&gt; void | undefined
  placeholder: string
}

const Input: React.FunctionComponent&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token tag&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token tag&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token class-name&quot;&gt;InputProps&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token plain-text&quot;&gt; = ({
  value, onChange, placeholder
}) =&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;token tag&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token tag&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;input&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token attr-name&quot;&gt;type&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token attr-value&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;&quot;&lt;/span&gt;text&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token attr-name&quot;&gt;placeholder&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token script language-javascript&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token script-punctuation punctuation&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;placeholder&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token attr-name&quot;&gt;onChange&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token script language-javascript&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token script-punctuation punctuation&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token parameter&quot;&gt;e&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;=&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token function&quot;&gt;onChange&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;e&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;/&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token plain-text&quot;&gt;

const isEmpty = (s: string) =&gt; s === &quot;&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now let&apos;s write our less abstract implementation of the form, with two different &lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;useState&lt;/code&gt;, one for each field, &lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;firstname&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;lastname&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;gatsby-highlight&quot; data-language=&quot;tsx&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;language-tsx&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-tsx&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; App&lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; React&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token function-variable function&quot;&gt;FC&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;=&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;firstname&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; setFirstname&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token function&quot;&gt;useState&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token string&quot;&gt;&quot;&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;lastname&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; setLastname&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token function&quot;&gt;useState&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token string&quot;&gt;&quot;&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;name&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; setName&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token function&quot;&gt;useState&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token string&quot;&gt;&quot;&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;err&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; setErr&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token function&quot;&gt;useState&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token boolean&quot;&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
  
  &lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; onChangeFirstname &lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;e&lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; React&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;ChangeEvent&lt;span class=&quot;token tag&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token tag&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token class-name&quot;&gt;HTMLInputElement&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token plain-text&quot;&gt;) =&gt; 
    setFirstname(e.target.value)
  
  const onChangeLastname = (e: React.ChangeEvent&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token tag&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token tag&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token class-name&quot;&gt;HTMLInputElement&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token plain-text&quot;&gt;) =&gt; 
    setLastname(e.target.value)
  
  const onSubmitAction = (e: React.FormEvent&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token tag&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token tag&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token class-name&quot;&gt;HTMLFormElement&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token plain-text&quot;&gt;) =&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
    e&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token function&quot;&gt;preventDefault&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;

    &lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token function&quot;&gt;isEmpty&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;firstname&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;||&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token function&quot;&gt;isEmpty&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;lastname&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;span class=&quot;token function&quot;&gt;setErr&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token boolean&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;span class=&quot;token function&quot;&gt;setName&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token string&quot;&gt;&quot;&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;span class=&quot;token keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
    
    &lt;span class=&quot;token function&quot;&gt;setName&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token template-string&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token template-punctuation string&quot;&gt;`&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token interpolation&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token interpolation-punctuation punctuation&quot;&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;firstname&lt;span class=&quot;token interpolation-punctuation punctuation&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token string&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token interpolation&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token interpolation-punctuation punctuation&quot;&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;lastname&lt;span class=&quot;token interpolation-punctuation punctuation&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token template-punctuation string&quot;&gt;`&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;token function&quot;&gt;setErr&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token boolean&quot;&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class=&quot;token punctuation&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token plain-text&quot;&gt;

  return (
